Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}. Drain and rinse
@black beans{13.4%ounce} and @corn{13.4%ounce}, keeping them separate.

Melt @butter{2%tablespoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add onion
and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup},
beans, and half the @southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}. Add @water{3/4%cup}
and @kosher salt{1%tsp}. Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce to a gentle simmer,
and cook until tender, ~{15%minutes}.

Heat a #medium pan{} over high heat. Pat corn dry with a #paper towel{}, removing
as much moisture as possible. Add corn to pan and cook, tossing occasionally,
until lightly charred, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cut @roma tomato{1} into small cubes. Zest 1 tsp zest from @lime{1} and cut into
quarters. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Toss tomato, corn, remaining Southwest
spice, half the cilantro, half the lime zest, juice from one lime quarter, and
a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #small bowl{}. Season with plenty
of salt and pepper.

Stir together @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, remaining lime zest, and a squeeze of
lime juice in another small bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Once rice is
done, fluff grains with a #fork{}. Stir in half the @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}.
Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with salsa. Garnish with remaining cheese
and cilantro. Dollop with crema and drizzle to taste with @hot sauce{1%teaspoon}.
Serve with @tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} for dipping and remaining lime for squeezing
over.